Neural Networks, Probabilistic Methods. 

Neural Networks: The paper discusses the use of autoencoders, which are a type of neural network, to model the manifolds of images of handwritten digits. The authors also mention using a convolutional neural network (CNN) for classification.

Probabilistic Methods: The paper uses a probabilistic model called a Gaussian mixture model (GMM) to represent the distribution of the latent variables in the autoencoder. The authors also use a probabilistic model called a variational autoencoder (VAE) to generate new images of digits.
